<section class="bright-section bright-section--basf-summary" aria-labelledby="basf-title">
  <div class="container">
    <h2 id="basf-title">What are some of our fundamental beliefs?</h2>

    <div class="basf-summary-panel">
      <ul class="basf-cards">
        <li class="basf-card">
          <span class="basf-card__badge" aria-hidden="true">1</span>
          <h3 class="basf-card__title">The Bible Is the Inspired Word of God</h3>
          <p class="basf-card__text">
            The Bible is the inspired Word of God and the only reliable authority for faith and life.
            Both the Old and New Testaments are essential for understanding God&rsquo;s purpose. The
            Scriptures reveal God&rsquo;s character, His plan for the earth, and the message of salvation
            through Jesus Christ. Regular bible reading and study are central to the life of a
            believer.
            <span class="basf-card__refs">(2&nbsp;Timothy 3:16&ndash;17, 2&nbsp;Peter 1:20&ndash;21, Psalm 119:105)</span>
          </p>
        </li>
        <li class="basf-card">
          <span class="basf-card__badge" aria-hidden="true">2</span>
          <h3 class="basf-card__title">There Is One God, the Father</h3>
          <p class="basf-card__text">
            There is one God, the Creator of heaven and earth. The Bible consistently identifies
            Him as the Father. Jesus Christ is His Son, and the Holy Spirit is understood as God&rsquo;s
            power at work rather than a separate divine person. For this reason, we do not accept
            the doctrine of the Trinity and instead emphasize the Bible&rsquo;s teaching that God is one.
            <span class="basf-card__refs">(Deuteronomy 6:4, Isaiah 45:5, John 17:3, 1&nbsp;Corinthians 8:6)</span>
          </p>
        </li>
        <li class="basf-card">
          <span class="basf-card__badge" aria-hidden="true">3</span>
          <h3 class="basf-card__title">Jesus Christ Is the Son of God and the Promised Messiah</h3>
          <p class="basf-card__text">
            Jesus Christ is the Son of God, born of the virgin Mary by the power of God. He lived a
            life of perfect obedience and revealed God&rsquo;s character through his teaching and
            example. Though fully human, he did not sin. Through his sacrificial death and
            resurrection, God opened the way for forgiveness of sins and the hope of eternal life for
            those who follow him.
            <span class="basf-card__refs">(Luke 1:31&ndash;35, Hebrews 4:15, Acts 2:22&ndash;24, Romans 5:8&ndash;10)</span>
          </p>
        </li>
        <li class="basf-card">
          <span class="basf-card__badge" aria-hidden="true">4</span>
          <h3 class="basf-card__title">Jesus Will Return to the Earth</h3>
          <p class="basf-card__text">
            God will one day soon send Jesus Christ back to earth. His return will bring judgment
            and the fulfillment of God&rsquo;s promises. The second coming of Christ is a central theme
            throughout the Bible and was a key part of the message preached by Jesus and the
            apostles.
            <span class="basf-card__refs">(Acts 1:11, Matthew 25:31&ndash;32, Revelation 11:15)</span>
          </p>
        </li>
        <li class="basf-card">
          <span class="basf-card__badge" aria-hidden="true">5</span>
          <h3 class="basf-card__title">God Will Establish His Kingdom on Earth</h3>
          <p class="basf-card__text">
            The Bible promises a future Kingdom of God on earth. When Jesus returns, he will reign
            as king and bring peace, justice, and righteousness to the nations. This Kingdom fulfills
            the promises God made to Abraham, David, and Israel and will ultimately extend
            throughout the whole world.
            <span class="basf-card__refs">(Daniel 2:44, Psalm 72:8&ndash;11, Luke 1:32&ndash;33, Genesis 12:1&ndash;3)</span>
          </p>
        </li>
        <li class="basf-card">
          <span class="basf-card__badge" aria-hidden="true">6</span>
          <h3 class="basf-card__title">The Gospel Concerns the Kingdom of God and the Name of Jesus Christ</h3>
          <p class="basf-card__text">
            The gospel message of the Bible centers on two connected themes: the coming
            Kingdom of God, and the saving work of Jesus Christ. This message runs throughout
            the entire Bible, from the promises made in the Old Testament to the preaching of Jesus
            and the apostles in the New Testament.
            <span class="basf-card__refs">(Mark 1:14&ndash;15, Acts 8:12, Galatians&nbsp;3:8, Luke 24:27)</span>
          </p>
        </li>
        <li class="basf-card">
          <span class="basf-card__badge" aria-hidden="true">7</span>
          <h3 class="basf-card__title">Salvation Comes Through Faith, Repentance, and Baptism</h3>
          <p class="basf-card__text">
            Individuals must respond to the gospel by believing its message, repenting of sin, and
            being baptized by full immersion in water. Baptism represents a conscious
            commitment to follow Jesus Christ. It symbolizes the forgiveness of sins and the
            beginning of a new life devoted to learning from the Bible and living according to
            Christ&rsquo;s teachings.
            <span class="basf-card__refs">(Acts 2:38, Mark 16:16, Romans 6:3&ndash;5, Acts 8:35&ndash;38)</span>
          </p>
        </li>
        <li class="basf-card">
          <span class="basf-card__badge" aria-hidden="true">8</span>
          <h3 class="basf-card__title">Death Is the End of Conscious Life</h3>
          <p class="basf-card__text">
            The Bible teaches that humans are mortal and that death is the end of conscious
            existence. The dead do not live in heaven or hell. Instead, the Bible describes death as
            a state like sleep, from which people will be awakened when Jesus returns and
            the resurrection takes place.
            <span class="basf-card__refs">(Ecclesiastes 9:5&ndash;6, Psalm 146:4, John 11:11&ndash;14, Daniel 12:2)</span>
          </p>
        </li>
        <li class="basf-card">
          <span class="basf-card__badge" aria-hidden="true">9</span>
          <h3 class="basf-card__title">Resurrection and Judgment Will Occur When Christ Returns</h3>
          <p class="basf-card__text">
            When Jesus returns, those who are responsible to God will be raised from the dead and
            judged. Those who have faithfully followed Christ will receive eternal life and will share
            in the blessings and work of God&rsquo;s Kingdom on earth.
            <span class="basf-card__refs">(John 5:28&ndash;29, Acts 17:31, 2&nbsp;Corinthians 5:10, Matthew 25:34)</span>
          </p>
        </li>
        <li class="basf-card">
          <span class="basf-card__badge basf-card__badge--wide" aria-hidden="true">10</span>
          <h3 class="basf-card__title">Followers of Christ Seek to Live by His Teachings</h3>
          <p class="basf-card__text">
            Believers must seek to follow the example and teachings of Jesus in everyday life. This
            includes practicing love, humility, honesty, and service to others. This includes
            fellowship and service with fellow believers, which encourages living in accordance to
            the message of the Bible.
            <span class="basf-card__refs">(John 13:34&ndash;35, Micah 6:8, Colossians 3:12&ndash;14, Hebrews 10:24&ndash;25)</span>
          </p>
        </li>
      </ul>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

{# <section class="bright-section bright-section--distinct" aria-labelledby="distinct-title">
  <div class="container">
    <h2 id="distinct-title">Some distinctive emphases</h2>
    <p class="bright-muted">
    We share much with other believers who love Scripture. A few areas where Christadelphian teaching is often distinctive include:
    </p>
    <ul class="distinct-grid">
      <li class="distinct-card">
        <h3>One God, the Father</h3>
        <p>We believe in the one God of the Bible; Jesus is the Son of God. The Holy Spirit is God&rsquo;s power, not a separate co-equal person in a trinity.</p>
      </li>
      <li class="distinct-card">
        <h3>Mortality and resurrection</h3>
        <p>We are mortal; eternal life is God&rsquo;s gift through resurrection, not an immortal soul leaving the body at death.</p>
      </li>
      <li class="distinct-card">
        <h3>The devil in Scripture</h3>
        <p>We read &ldquo;devil&rdquo; and related language in context&mdash;often referring to sin and opposition to God rather than a personal supernatural evil being.</p>
      </li>
      <li class="distinct-card">
        <h3>Kingdom on earth</h3>
        <p>God&rsquo;s kingdom is the restored rule of Christ on earth, centered in the promises to Israel, not a disembodied heaven-only hope.</p>
      </li>
      <li class="distinct-card">
        <h3>Conditional immortality</h3>
        <p>Life everlasting is for those in Christ; those who finally reject God are destroyed, not tortured forever.</p>
      </li>
      <li class="distinct-card">
        <h3>Baptism</h3>
        <p>We baptize believers by full immersion as a response to the gospel, following New Testament practice.</p>
      </li>
    </ul>
  </div>
</section> #}

